      "stem_html": "<p>Cyclooctatetraene was first synthesized in 1911 by a route that involved the following transformation:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbndhIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1cf75b3bbf1967dc803bd211c3d21f20a73ec3d6/OChem_24_EC_055.jpg\" alt=\"9-Methyl-9-azabicyclo[3.3.1]non-2-ene is separated from 1,3,5-cyclooctatriene by an arrow.\">\n<p>How might you use the Hofmann elimination to accomplish this reaction? How would you finish the synthesis by converting cyclooctatriene into cyclooctatetraene?</p>",
